article.headline: New Mexico State 83, Utah State 77
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Elijah Ingram scored 24 points and Mike Mitchell scored 23 to lead New Mexico State to a 83-77 win over Utah State on Saturday night. Tyrone Nelson added 16 points and David Fisher scored 13 points and pulled down a game-high 12 rebounds for New Mexico State (10-12, 6-5 Western Athletic Conference). New Mexico State made nine free throws down the stretch to the sweep the season series against the WAC's other Aggies. Utah State (16-6, 7-4) was led by Durrall Peterson with 21 points and seven rebounds. Nate Harris finished with 18 points for Utah State. Utah State led by five points midway through the second half, but was outscored 14-8 in the game's final three minutes. An unforced turnover in the final 90 seconds stalled Utah State's comeback and led to more free throws by New Mexico State. Jaycee Carroll scored 32 points in a 93-86 loss at Las Cruces, N.M., but managed only 11 points on 4-of-9 shooting at home. New Mexico State pulled down 17 offensive rebounds, two in the game's final three minutes that led to baskets, and finished with a 35-29 rebounding advantage. Utah State never led in the first half until the 2:15 mark when David Pak hit a 3-pointer for a 34-33 lead. New Mexico State then regained the lead, but a buzzer-beating 3-pointer by Pak gave Utah State a 39-38 lead at halftime.
